=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Start from the NH fused diazine core bearing a chloromethyl handle; N-alkylate the ring N with 2-bromoethyl ethyl ether to give the N-(2-ethoxyethyl) chloromethyl core | Step 2: SN2 substitution of the chloromethyl group with mono-Boc-piperazine to form the core–CH2–N(Boc)piperazine intermediate | Step 3: Remove Boc to give the deprotected core–CH2–piperazine intermediate | Step 4 (branch): Prepare the side-chain electrophile by SNAr of an activated chloro fused aza-heteroaryl with 2-bromoethylamine to obtain BrCH2CH2NH–c3nc4cnccc4[nH]3 | Step 5: Final N-alkylation of the free piperazine nitrogen with this bromide furnishes the exact target, CCOCCn1c(CN2CCN(CCNc3nc4cnccc4[nH]3)CC2)nc2cccnc21

